value.name: 92 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 92 (ninety-two) is the natural number following 91 and preceding 93. In mathematics [ edit ] 92 is the eighth pentagonal number , [1] and an Erdős–Woods number , since it is possible to find sequences of 92 consecutive integers such that each inner member shares a factor with either the first or the last member.
